OL,3,CWhere do the parties stand on key
OL,4,Cissues & controversies in the Border
OL,5,Cregion?
OL,7,FLabour say the party "does not support
OL,8,Findependence or another referendum".
OL,9,FThey pledge to "protect and respect
OL,10,Fdevolution and reset relations"
OL,11,Fbetween the governments at Westminster
OL,12,Fand Holyrood.
OL,14,FThe Liberal Democrats say they "oppose
OL,15,Fa second Scottish independence
OL,16,Freferendum and independence". They are
OL,17,Fpledging to "introduce a written
OL,18,Fconstitution for a federal United
OL,19,FKingdom with strong voices for
OL,20,FEngland, Wales, Scotland and Northern
OL,21,FIreland".
