OL,3,CWhere do the parties stand on key
OL,4,Cissues & controversies in the Border
OL,5,Cregion?
OL,7,FThe Conservatives say that, if they
OL,8,Fare re-elected, they will deliver on
OL,9,Fpledges previously made in government,
OL,10,Fsuch as upgrading the Cumbrian coast
OL,11,Frailway line. They say they would
OL,12,Fprovide "guaranteed investment" to
OL,13,Fimprove pinch points on the A75
OL,14,Fbetween Gretna and Stranraer, and
OL,15,Fpoint to #5m for evaluating proposals
OL,16,Fto extend the Borders Railway from
OL,17,FTweedbank through Hawick to Carlisle.
OL,18,FThey also say they would "pursue the
OL,19,Fextension" of a low-tax 'Enhanced
OL,20,FInvestment Zone' planned for Northern
OL,21,FIreland to also cover Stranraer and
OL,22,FCairnryan.
